Numerical Note: YHWH (יהוה) = 26 base. YHYYH variant = 36 intensified (doubled Yod for covenant/redemptive emphasis). Literal root fidelity to Nag Hammadi Coptic/Greek fragments with YHWH framework alignment.

The disciples went their way to preach the Gospel. They were filled with joy and gave thanks to YHWH. This is the secret book of James.
James said: “Be sober and do not be led astray. The Savior has revealed these things to us so that we may know the truth and be saved from the error of the world.”
The Savior said: “Do not be grieved because of the multitude of sins. The kingdom is like a grain of wheat. When it falls on prepared ground, it brings forth a great ear. So also with you: when you are sown in the world, you will be gathered into the kingdom.”
The Savior said: “Blessed is the one who has come to know the Father and has become like the Father. Such a one will not taste death.”
The Savior said: “I have come to reveal the things that are hidden. The rulers of this world do not know the Father. They have created the world of matter to keep souls in bondage. But the Light will return to its root.”
James said: “Lord, how shall we pray?” The Savior said: “Pray to the Father in secret, and the Father who sees in secret will reward you openly.”
The Savior said: “The kingdom of YHWH is within you. Seek it and you will find it. Knock and it will be opened to you.”
The Savior said: “I am the Light that is above all. I am the All. From Me the All came forth and to Me the All will return.”
James said: “Lord, tell us about the end.” The Savior said: “The end is the beginning. When you return to the root from which you came, you will be saved.”
The Savior said: “Do not let this world deceive you. The flesh is temporary. The spirit is eternal. Those who cling to the flesh will perish with it. Those who awaken to the spirit will live forever.”
The Savior said: “Peace I leave with you. My peace I give to you. Not as the world gives do I give to you. Let not your hearts be troubled.”
James said: “We have received these words in secret. We will guard them and pass them to those who are worthy.”
The Savior said: “Write these things down and hide them. They are not for this generation but for the elect who will come after.”
The Savior said: “I have given you the mystery of the kingdom. Keep it pure and do not cast it before swine.”
The Savior said: “Blessed are those who have not seen and yet have believed. Greater is their reward.”
The Savior said: “I am going to the place from which I came. Follow Me in spirit and you will sit with Me in the kingdom of YHWH.”
And after saying these things, the Savior departed from them and ascended into heaven.

And when He had said these things, He departed from us. But we remained in great joy and gave thanks to the Father who had sent His Son to us, glorifying YHWH for the revelation He had granted.
The disciples said to one another: “Let us pray and ask the Lord for further revelation.” And as they prayed, the heavens opened and the Savior appeared again.
James and Peter received this secret book from the Lord. They wrote it down and sent it to the one who asked for it, that he too might understand the hidden mysteries of the kingdom.
The Lord appeared to His disciples after His resurrection and spoke with them, revealing many things which are not written in the other books.
This is the secret book which the Savior revealed to James and Peter while they were together with the other disciples. He spoke to them in parables and openly about the kingdom.
